  "text": "Found retry with exponential backoff implementations across all three repos:\n\n**kubernetes/kubernetes**: The core `wait.ExponentialBackoff` function is defined in `staging/src/k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/util/wait/backoff.go` along with `ExponentialBackoffWithContext` and `NewExponentialBackoffManager`. These are used extensively across the codebase: webhook retry logic in `apiserver/pkg/util/webhook/webhook.go`, goroutine map backoff in `pkg/util/goroutinemap/exponentialbackoff/`, volume operations in CSI/PV controllers, kubelet plugin/volume reconcilers, kube-proxy, certificate manager, reflector, and admission controllers. The `client-go/util/retry/util.go` provides a retry utility using the same backoff primitives.\n\n**grafana/grafana**: Multiple retrier implementations: (1) `pkg/util/retryer/retryer.go` - a simple `Retry()` function with exponential backoff used by sqlstore, cloud migration, and dashboard services; (2) `pkg/services/ngalert/schedule/retry.go` - `exponentialBackoffRetryer` struct wrapping cenkalti/backoff, used by alert and recording rule evaluation; (3) `pkg/registry/apis/provisioning/resources/retry_client.go` - `retryWithBackoff` using k8s `wait.ExponentialBackoff`; (4) `apps/provisioning/pkg/repository/git/repository.go` - `defaultGitRetrier` using nanogit's `ExponentialBackoffRetrier`; (5) gRPC retry interceptors in `pkg/storage/unified/client_retry.go`, `pkg/server/ring.go`, `pkg/services/apiserver/options/storage.go`, and `pkg/registry/apis/secret/decrypt/grpc_client.go` using `grpc_retry.BackoffExponentialWithJitter`; (6) `apps/advisor/pkg/app/checktyperegisterer/checktyperegisterer.go` with manual exponential backoff; (7) `pkg/services/ngalert/remote/client/alertmanager.go` with `IsReadyWithBackoff`; (8) `pkg/services/sqlstore/migrator/migrator.go` and `pkg/storage/unified/resource/server.go` using dskit backoff.\n\n**prometheus/prometheus**: The remote write backoff is in `storage/remote/queue_manager.go` via `sendWriteRequestWithBackoff()` which implements exponential backoff with min/max bounds (doubling sleep: `backoff = min(sleepDuration*2, MaxBackoff)`), respecting `Retry-After` headers. `storage/remote/client.go` defines `RecoverableError` and `Store()` which returns recoverable errors for 5xx/429 responses. Backoff config (`MinBackoff`/`MaxBackoff`) is defined in `config/config.go` under `QueueConfig`.",
